name: jungle jim
text: The philly steaks were cooked fast, but far from perfection. It was dripping of grease, bread was soggy, the side of fries were soggy, none of it tasted fresh, lacking cheese, the drink served didnt have any ice

name: Juan Rosario
text: I ordered the whiz kid and it was very disappointing. The sandwich was very unsatisfying to eat. The “philly cheese steak” is not authentic and it is very expensive compared to a real Philly cheesesteak. 15$ for a hero, fries, and a soda in which the portion was not justified and the flavor was so uncultured.

name: Kashton Hinton
text: This spot is the one I like best. I eat in a lot of restaurants but to this place I go the most. The stuff is very affectionate and the cuisine they place on your table is so flavorful. I never miss an opportunity to have a nice dinner here. Highly recommended.

name: Caleb Ware
text: Fantastic and flavorful food, I like the mood the spot has, and the workers were welcoming. I will definitely visit here when I’m around.

name: Armando Mata
text: The service is consistently quick, excellent character, very friendly employees. I will visit here again when I am here.

name: Colin Cumiskey
text: ,, this is the worst fast-food experience I have ever had in my life, the guy said he was one of the most ignorant people I have ever came across in my life,, 0 customer skills,, everything was an effort …More

name: CYBERTZAR
text: The food was pretty decent. But really overpriced, we ordered like 3 philly cheese steaks and 3 drinks for 50 fricking dollars. The employees are bad, have no attitude, and are just so agrivating. I will never dine here again.

name: Chipmunk Almond
text: Don't call it as a cheesesteaks from philly. Definitly not even close as phillyscheeseteaks food. I ordered the one called "The loaded philly". Come on... putting fries in the sandwich is good idea but your fries taste bad. It just dont …More

text: Nice and freshly made every day!

name: Al Pa
text: The food is good but the employees attitude is not good

name: Lionel
text: It was ok.  The food was hot. The meat really under seasoned. A big disappointing really. Large portion though.

name: Jeff Hunk
text: Bread (hoagie) was too soggy from (thawed) vegetables, and the meat can't be really called steak. They use the lowest grade meat with a lot of tendons & ligaments, so it feels like chewing on the shoe sole with fat rather than meat but still overpriced for the quality.

name: Cemal S
text: Defiantly not a good cheese steak. Bread was old and meat was uncooked. They put more veggies than the meat itself and this meat not a sirloin steak. I couldn't eat it after first bite.
